				\begin{document}$${{{{{\rm{O}}}}}}-{{{{{\rm{H}}}}}}\cdots {{{{{\rm{I}}}}}}^{-}$$\end{document}) at the grain boundary. This interaction hinders the diffusion of iodide ions, restricts the formation of iodine vacancies (by increasing the atomic ratio of iodine ion (I:Sn) in the surface of FASnI3) and decreases the ionic conductivity (σion)99, 116. Moreover, the polymer addition favours the formation of nucleation sites in the Sn-HP, reducing the trap states and slowing down the crystal growth99.
